  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Multicenter, double blind, randomized trial to assess the effect of low-dose colchicine
      (0.5mg/day) on overall mortality, new coronary syndromes, and ischemic stroke at 2 years
      after an acute coronary syndrome. The study hypothesis is that colchicine may reduce the
      specified combined endpoint from 16% to 7-8% at a 2-years follow-up.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Multicenter, double-blind randomized trial to evaluate the efficacy of low dose colchicine
      (0.5mg once daily for 2 years) to reduce the incidence of subsequent overall mortality, new
      acute coronary syndromes, and ischemic stroke in patients admitted for an acute coronary
      syndrome.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
